Description: I initially joined Missouri as a consultant soon after the agency was founded by Stuart Wood & Paul Brennan, and worked closely with them for 4 years to establish the business. Although one of a number of agencies I worked with, Missouri soon became more than just another client. I love working with Stu & Paul for their strategic and creative brilliance (and sense of humour). So much so that after a 3 year hiatus, I've re-joined in a full-time, strategic role to help deliver our 5 year growth plan.Coming from big agency backgrounds, we see the opportunity to create a new kind of agency; one that's more responsive to the increasingly frenetic pace of changing consumer behaviour and customer demands, and is unbound by the traditional, siloed thinking so often seen in big agency cultures.This combination allows us to think big, act fast and deliver the service clients are looking for in today’s competitive marketplace. Small agency agility with large agency experience.Missouri's success has been driven by our mantra, ‘Don’t tell me, show me’. Why? Because in today’s experience economy, successful brands can no longer TELL consumers why, they have to SHOW them. (Missouri is the 'Show Me state', hence the name.)In the 8 years since I helped get Missouri started, the team has worked across categories and continents. We've been the pan-European brand and retail communications agency for Foot Locker Europe and worked extensively with multiple brands in the Pernod Ricard portfolio – most notably an 8-year relationship with Jameson Irish whiskey as their global below-the-line agency of record, helping to increase sales by an average of 14% YOY in that time.Other notable clients include Honda, Carlsberg Group, Marriott, TUI Group, RNLI, Estée Lauder, Paddy Power, Asics, Snow+Rock, Harlequins Rugby Club and UK Sport.We've won multiple awards for our work, including 5 Transform Europe awards, a Design Week Gold for our work with Chivas Regal and The Drum’s Branding and Design Agency of the Year.Missouri is a team of multi-disciplinary thinkers, creators and doers from diverse cultural backgrounds, building a powerful agency culture and creating long term relationships with clients. Our unique approach delivers compelling experiences and identities for consumers, and tangible business results for clients. Whether online, in-store, on-shelf or on pack, we understand how, through memorable, emotive design and communication, brands can create impact where it matters most, where the brand meets the consumer.We’d love to SHOW YOU how.Drop me a line!I initially joined Missouri as a consultant soon after the agency was founded by Stuart Wood & Paul Brennan, and worked closely with them for 4 years to establish the business. Headline: Founder
Description: Founder and owner of ALL Creative; an independent strategic brand and communications agency delivering powerful creative thinking that cuts through complexity. My team and I thrive on brand and product marketing challenges that are awkward and tricky. We deliver creative solutions that are built on strategic insight. That’s why we specialise in sectors including health, science and technology, and visitor destinations. My agency is built on 30+ years agency experience working for large multinationals, SMEs and entrepreneurs to realise and refine their brand identity solutions. During this time I have worked for some of the world's leading brand communication agencies and have directed campaigns for the likes of Boehringer Ingelheim, Diageo, GSK, Novartis, Perrigo, Pfizer, Procter & Gamble and Unilever.If your company has complex branding and communication needs and you need help demystifying the fog, we can help. Description: A strategy director with over a decade's experience, I spend my time devising insight-driven strategies, leading a team and consulting clients. Working with the likes of tech brands and NGOs, this involves everything from integrated campaign strategy, digital marketing and paid media plans all the way through to narrative and messaging development.For me, strategy is about bringing together art and science. As an English grad and former journalist, my work requires deep audience understanding, creativity, and a good pinch of wordsmithery—“the art”. Then, as a critical thinker and number lover, I equally thrive on the science of analysing data, building processes and devising strategies that solve for business problems.Most recently, I’ve been responsible for devising an end-to-end approach to digital content strategy.
